        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>Located in Water Valley, MS, Base Camp Coding Academy (BCCA) is a hands-on, challenging and fun program, designed
            to train students to be software developers in 12 months.</p>
        <p>In a small classroom setting, you will work with real world technologies to learn the fundamentals of coding, app
            development and the life leadership skills you will need to be successful in your career and competitive in the
            job market.</p>
        <h2>What does it take to attend Base Camp Coding Academy?</h2>
        <h4>Step 1: Nomination</h4>
        <p>Any Mississippi student in their senior year may be nominated by an unrelated adult with insight into the student’s aptitude and motivation. </br>
        We are accepting nominations from January 4th, 2021 through April 2nd, 2021: <a href="https://forms.gle/o3zLY36McHc2A68UA" target="_blank">Nomination Form</a></p>
        <h4>Step 2: Application and Interviews</h4>
        <p>Through the application and interviews, the students will have a chance to demonstrate their abilities and determination.</p>
        <h4>Step 3: Show Up, and Work Hard</h4>
        <p>Commit to working with your peers every weekday for 12 months to master this skill set.</p>
        <h4>Step 4: Graduate, and Land a Great Job</h4>
        <p>Base Camp’s goal is to provide as many opportunities as possible for our students to leave the program with a job offer in hand and be successful in their careers.</p>
        <h4>Step 5: Be Exceptional</h4>
        <p>Every graduate carries the reputation of Base Camp with them into the workforce. We expect them to represent!</p>
        <h2>What don’t you need to attend Base Camp Coding Academy?</h2>
        <h4>Money.</h4>
        <p>Every student accepted into Base Camp Coding Academy receives a 100% scholarship.</p>
        <p>Thanks to the generous support of Mississippi’s business and philanthropic leaders, Base Camp Coding Academy is a
            not for profit 501(c)(3) program.</p>
